I've been to many Dunkin Donuts in many areas and this review is specifically for this one area. From what I have noticed on several occasions the staff behind the counter is extremely friendly and even make the customer part of the employees conversation. Small talk goes a long way for me. I usually walk in around 7 o'clock in the morning and along with the friendly employee atmosphere the music volume is slightly turned higher than normal which is what I like and it fits the mood in the morning.  Also, the friendly employees seems to be contagious and not just from one particular employee. It all the employees.  For customer Service skills I give this an A+ For Food -  Average Dunkin Donut Tasting For Coffee - The best taste you can get from this food chain Large ordering - Employees are very keen and smart to understanding a large order you them, and they actually use the markings on the drinks to check off sugar or milk, where most places ignore the markings on the cups. My bottom line: As a morning coffe seeker, expect a welcoming atmosphere with great in the mood employees and slightly louder good music. So if you need your morning coffee and need to break the Ice with the on the way to work morning blues, this atmosphere is perfect for that.
